f_djb_VZUrM.title: A Country Without Birthdays?!
f_djb_VZUrM.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

I've come to Bhutan. I've asked several people when they were born, and they couldn't give me an answer... because they don't know. 

Why?

The Bhutanese genuinely believe that leading a happy life is more important than how many years you’ve been alive (birthday). If that doesn't make you smile, then I don't know what will :)

Instead of recognizing individual birthdays – they decided that all citizens turn 1 year older every Jan 1st. So everyone celebrates a birthday on New Year's Day! 

While this system is more prevalent in the older generation (younger kids living in cities do know their birthdays) -- it's still proves how fascinating this country is. I've never been to a place where people don't know their birthdays, and don't care to know. They just want to life in peace.

The sun rises everyday. The sun sets everyday. Life happens. Age doesn't matter. That's Bhutan in a nutshell. And I love this country.

rNF8Q6yDAC8.title: Top 7 Countries in Asia!
rNF8Q6yDAC8.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

Asia has been my home since 2013, when I moved to South Korea to teach English. Over the last 5 years, I've lived in Vietnam, the Philippines and currently Thailand -- and I've been to almost every country on the beautiful continent of Asia.

Each culture in Asia is very unique -- from religions to traditions, nature, history, cuisines and rituals -- and it provides endless opportunities to learn and discover. But above anything else, THE PEOPLE of Asia are the most hospitable and welcoming as they come. 

Admittedly, it has been very hard to choose only 7 of my favorite Asian countries to feature in this video (because I truly love every place for a different reason) -- but when it all comes down to it, these would be my 7 favorite countries on this amazing place called Asia!

THE PHILIPPINES SOUTH KOREA, SINGAPORE, VIETNAM, NEPAL, INDONESIA, JAPAN

What would be your top 7 in Asia? Why? Please comment below and let's get the discussion started! 

PS - I kept this video limited to East/South/Southeast Asian countries. While the Middle East and West/Central Asia are technically Asian countries, I consider them very culturally different. Iran and Tajikstan would be on this list if it was all of Asia!

tWc3cIWtB7o.title: I Just Spent $7,000 on Flights to Africa...
tWc3cIWtB7o.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

I just spent the most money I've EVER spent in one single day. Seven thousand United States dollars ($7,000 USD). I'm so full of emotions right now (excited, nervous, happy, anxious) that I'm not sure how to react...

The $7,000 was spent on flights to less-touristy countries in Central and West Africa which I will be visiting by myself in Sept/Oct: Namibia, Angola, São Tomé and Príncipe, Gabon, Cameroon, Equatorial Guinea, Chad, Mali and Mauritania.

The most nerve-racking part about all of this is that I need to have these flight confirmations to start applying for 4 visas right now (Angola, Cameroon, Chad & Mali) -- and if any of those 4 African visas get denied, then I will have to cancel a portion of the trip and I will not get reimbursed for the flight costs. High risk, high reward!

In case you are wondering, I made this video for a few reasons:

A) I like to be honest & transparent with you in all my videos, and budgeting is very important for any traveler

B) I think it's often overlooked how expensive traveling to Africa is, so I want to tell you (again) the reality of traveling on this continent. Sure, you CAN do it on the cheaper side, but I don't have the time to go overland or the energy to sleep in dirty hostels. I also need access to (the best) wifi everyday so I can work and upload videos!

Truth be told, I am really excited for this trip and to witness the hidden cultures in these African countries first-hand. Have you ever been to any of these 9 countries in Africa? I will gladly take some tips/advice or any local connection!

I've flown more than 100 different airlines around the world, and no airline is better than the one I flew today, Emirates!!

(This video is not sponsored. I just want to share how incredible the experience is flying with Emirates!)

For many reasons, Emirates is always my airline of choice (I've flown them about 15 times) -- I'm telling you that flying Economy Class on Emirates is better than Business Class on most other airlines!

The entertainment screen on Emirates Economy has more movies, TV shows, documentaries, podcasts and live TV options for FREE than you could ever want. The food is as fresh it gets. The flight attendants' hospitality and overall service on Emirates flights is on another level (especially when comparing to any American-owned airlines). 

Has anyone reading this flown Emirates before, and can agree that they are the best? If you don't think they are the World's best airline, then what do you think is?

MQRROshum2s.title: I Just Turned 27 & All I Want to do is TRAVEL
MQRROshum2s.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

When I took my first trip overseas in college (January, 2010) -- I had no idea how much influence it would have on my life. I did not realize that it ignited a massive travel bug inside my heart!!

Fast forward 8 years, and I just turned 27 years old. I have now been to 140 countries and I'm closing in on my goal to visit every single country in the world.

Travel has provided me a lot more enjoyment than just looking at famous landmarks and going scuba diving.

It has taught me about culture. About people. About traditions. About respect. Travel has shaped my perspectives. It has taught me to be simple. SctnYcKQb-U.title: A Disaster Day in The SEYCHELLES...
SctnYcKQb-U.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

Today, in the Seychelles, has been a complete disaster. Nothing has gone right. And I am very frustrated.

This morning, I woke up at 5AM ready to explore Mahé island (the main island of the Seychelles), but a rain storm came rolling through which forced me to delay the morning start until 9:30. When I hopped on the bus to the beach, there was a bad car accident in the road, causing another hour delay and everybody freaking out. Finally, I made it to the beach, only to discover everything being closed because it's a National Holiday today in the Seychelles. So I went to the capital town of Victoria, which was more like a ghost town as no restaurants or stores are open. I managed to find a small shop to get snacks, and while I was inside the store, I witnessed a bad street fight happening between two drunk people outside.  That's what I call a disaster in the Seychelles.

Despite being really frustrated and upset, I realized that none of these events have been in my control -- and that's why I should not hate the Seychelles.

This also is a reminder not hate ANY place based on unexpected events that happen out of your control (bad weather, breaking your arm, public holidays, etc).

Similar unfortunate events have happened to me in other countries, like Bulgaria, Brunei and India -- and when these situations happen, we need to be mature and move on. It's all part of the travel experience.

While 95% of my videos are positive and happy, I think it's important to show you the negative (more realistic) side of travel like my experience in the Seychelles... Because truth be told, for every good experience that happens on the road, something bad happens. I never tell you about all the travel delays, missed flights, and scams that I constantly deal with!

Can anyone out there relate to what I am saying in this video? Please comment with your thoughts and/or share your experiences of unfortunate events that have happened to you while traveling. I'm curious to know!

zMFRvtkTSHo.title: TODAY, THE WORLD WON! (13 Boys Saved in Thai Cave)
zMFRvtkTSHo.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

BREAKING NEWS: All 12 kids and their soccer coach were successfully rescued after 18 days of being miles deep inside a flooding Thai cave in Northern Thailand!! Everyone is celebrating where I am currently in Bangkok!!!

I am thrilled to be reporting this story to you, as it has taken a complete GLOBAL EFFORT to secure the lives of these innocent kids stuck in the Thai cave. Dozens and dozens of cave experts and specialist divers flew in from all corners of the world on their own dime, to help the cause.

This story makes me really happy, and it is just one (of the very few) headlines that make mass media.

Today, the world won.

Please join me in thanking all the helpers who joined forces in Northern Thailand to make this miracle happen in the Thai cave for these 13 young adults. And let's send our thoughts and prayers to the one Thai Navy Seal who died from running out of oxygen while attempting to rescue them. What a true hero.

All footage is taken from CNN, CBS, Thai TV, Express and BBC on their respective websites and Youtube channels.

jouXK_o53hg.title: 5 Things You Didn't Know About MAURITIUS
jouXK_o53hg.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

https://www.instagram.com/drewbinsky

BONZOUR from the beautiful African island nation of MAURITIUS!

(I didn't misspell 'Bonzour,' it means 'Hello' in their language of Creole, which is very similar to French) ;)

If you are like I was a few days ago, then you don't know much about this hidden country of Mauritius, which lies off the south eastern coast of Africa.

But after getting in touch with some locals from Mauritius who have kindly introduced me to their culture and showed me around the island -- I have put together this video which highlights the most interesting things I've learned about Mauritius so far. 

Have you ever been to Mauritius or know anything about Mauritian culture? What is your favorite part about the country?

Special thanks to Mauritius Tourism for inviting us, Solana Beach Mauritius for hosting us and My Moris for the delicioud street food tour!

Kos0slg2FdU.title: We've Arrived in Our 7th Continent.. TOGETHER!
Kos0slg2FdU.description:
📲 My JUST GO APP is here! Connect w/ travelers for free: https://apple.co/3vYPr75 
✅ SUBSCRIBE for more travel videos: https://bit.ly/3iAZlnw

Earlier this morning, Deanna and I arrived in MAURITIUS, which means that we have officially visited all 7th Continents TOGETHER (Yes, Mauritius is a country in Africa and yes, we went to Antarctica last October!) 

It's been incredible to see the world by her side, and we are thrilled to be able to say that we've experienced 42 countries and 7 continents together. 

HOW DID WE DO THIS?

While it may not appear this way from the the outside (i.e. watching videos) -- we both work VERY HARD online behind the scenes to make our dreams become a reality. We are behind our computer screens 8-10 hours a day, grinding in coffee shops, hotel lobbys, airport lounges and anywhere else where there is a wifi signal. We fund 100% of our travels through our online jobs. 

I am not making this video to brag, but to hopefully inspire some of you that you can do this too if you set your mind towards it.
